00:04:16.441 --> 00:04:19.407
a moment ago that they're actually paid for performance,

106
00:04:19.407 --> 00:04:20.921
which is a highly subjective thing,

107
00:04:20.921 --> 00:04:22.564
and also, wouldn't that,

108
00:04:22.564 --> 00:04:25.444
because you only have 10 or 15 minutes with the patient,

109
00:04:25.444 --> 00:04:27.300
wouldn't that have to start showing itself

110
00:04:27.300 --> 00:04:32.142
as the relief of the symptoms, almost?

111
00:04:32.142 --> 00:04:34.425
<v ->Well, it shows itself as the relief of the symptoms,</v>

112
00:04:34.425 --> 00:04:35.856
but that's not really true.

113
00:04:35.856 --> 00:04:37.925
In the environments that use paper performance,

114
00:04:37.925 --> 00:04:39.909
the highly-managed environments,

115
00:04:39.909 --> 00:04:42.898
it's more about the numbers.

116
00:04:42.898 --> 00:04:44.455
How low is the cholesterol?

117
00:04:44.455 --> 00:04:47.463
How well-controlled is the diabetes?

118
00:04:47.463 --> 00:04:50.868
Not how the patient experienced the visit, okay?

119
00:04:50.868 --> 00:04:51.731
Whereas if you look at

120
00:04:51.731 --> 00:04:54.762
actual patient satisfaction with their visits,

121
00:04:54.762 --> 00:04:56.648
it's a relationship-based experience.

122
00:04:56.648 --> 00:04:57.565
<v Regina>Absolutely.</v>

123
00:04:57.565 --> 00:04:59.896
<v ->So it's, "How did I like this person?"</v>

